headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic recorded 25 points, 12 rebounds and nine assists, finishing an assist shy of his 13th triple-double of the season, to help lead the Denver Nuggets to a 117-109 victory against the Indiana Pacers on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic leads balanced offensive effort in Nuggets' 117-109 win over Pacers

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 24 points, 10 rebounds and seven assists, helping the Miami Heat beat the Charlotte Hornets 104-87 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bam Adebayo stars as the Miami Heat beat the Charlotte Hornets 104-87

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard swished a 3-pointer at the buzzer in overtime to give the Milwaukee Bucks a stunning 143-142 win over the Sacramento Kings on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks stun Kings on Lillard's buzzer-beating 3-pointer in overtime

headlines.shortLinkText: T-wolves hold off Clippers 109-105 with big help from Edwards and Gobert

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Devin Booker had 34 points and the Phoenix Suns held off the Portland Trail Blazers 127-116 on Sunday night for their second straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 34 points, Suns hold off Trail Blazers 127-116
